                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Italy/289</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Phillips</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-03">June 3,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At the President’s request, I submitted this draft reply to Rome<note n="49"
                        xml:id="d484fn49">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note> to Secretary Morgenthau at the Treasury this afternoon. We discussed the
                    whole matter from various angles and Mr. Morgenthau agreed entirely to the
                    Department’s draft instructions. I thereupon called up the White House and asked
                    Mr. McIntyre to convey this message to the President inasmuch as the latter had
                    just left the offices. Mr. McIntyre promised to do so at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
